HEADWORD: Spatangoidea
<hw>Spat`an*goi"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Spatangus</er>, and <er>-oid</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An order of irregular sea urchins, usually having a more or less
heart-shaped shell with four or five petal-like ambulacra above. The
mouth is edentulous and situated anteriorly, on the under
side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spatangus</ent>⟦br⟧
